                     <unittitle>1795-1877. Family correspondence, 1795-1803, among Roger Minott Sherman, his brother, Josiah, and sister, Betsey Mitchell [Mrs. John Mitchell?], including a letter from Roger M. Sherman at Yale College, 1795, and an account of Sherman family history. The book continues with letters from Henry Sherman to his father, Josiah, and Yale memorabilia relating to the class of 1829, including bills, clippings and programs. For the period 1833-1877, the scrapbook contains social items (invitations, valentines, programs), verses by Henry Sherman, and family and business correspondence following his career from Albany to New York to Hartford and finally to Washington, D.C. Also included are clippings, reviews and correspondence relating to his book, <title render="italic">
                           <part>Slavery in the United States</part>
                        </title>, first published in 1858.</unittitle>
