                  level="file">
                  <did>
                     <unittitle>1836-1847. Scrapbook of literary extracts from contemporary newspapers. "The scraps were collected by Miss Anna Mary Mandall of Albany, now Mrs. Robert Minturn of New York. She presented them to me about a fortnight before she was married, on condition that I have them neatly pasted in 'a Scrap Book', to which I assented and received them. Some months after, I became acquainted with Miss Mary Camp, a beautiful 'girl of sixteen,' at Albany from Sackett's Harbour. She requested me to write a piece of original Poetry in the Album. I consented on condition that she would paste 'some scraps' I had in a book for me, to which she promised &amp; thus I secured the fulfillment of my engagement with my fair friend and the donor of them. So this volume commemorates the kindness of two female friends." [Signed] Henry Sherman.</unittitle>
